hands_on_practices.solution:
1. In the rest frame S′ the dispersion is 
$$k'(\omega')=\frac{n'(\omega')\,\omega'}{c},\qquad n'(\omega')=-\sqrt{A-\frac{B}{(\omega')^2}}\,. $$
The group velocity in S′ is 
$$v'_g=\frac{d\omega'}{dk'}=\Bigl(\frac{dk'}{d\omega'}\Bigr)^{-1}
=\frac{c}{n'+\omega'\,\frac{dn'}{d\omega'}}\,. $$

2. Compute 
$$\frac{dn'}{d\omega'}=-\frac12\frac{1}{\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}\cdot\frac{2B}{(\omega')^3}
=-\frac{B}{(\omega')^3\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}\,. $$
Hence
$$n'+\omega'\,\frac{dn'}{d\omega'}
=-\sqrt{A-\frac{B}{(\omega')^2}}-\frac{B}{(\omega')^2\,\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}
=-\frac{A}{\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}\,. $$

3. Thus 
$$v'_g=\frac{c}{-\tfrac{A}{\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}}
=-\frac{c}{A}\sqrt{A-\frac{B}{(\omega')^2}}\,. $$

4. Transform to the laboratory frame S by Lorentz velocity addition (pulse moving along x):
$$v_g=\frac{v+v'_g}{1+\frac{v\,v'_g}{c^2}}
=\frac{v-\frac{c}{A}\sqrt{A-\frac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}
{1-\frac{v}{c^2}\,\frac{c}{A}\sqrt{A-\frac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}
=\frac{v-\tfrac{c}{A}\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}
{1-\tfrac{v}{A\,c}\sqrt{A-\tfrac{B}{(\omega')^2}}}\,. $$
